profile_data.summary:
I'm passionate individual with a curious mindset to derive solutions from various scenarios. Currently a grad student at Northeastern University with 2.5+ years of work experience in the Health Science sector. As a Data Analyst in Cognizant , with a blend of expertise in Data and Electronics ,I bring a multifaceted approach to solving complex data challenges. My journey from EEE to data engineering has equipped me with a rare combination of hardware understanding and software proficiency.

My background in EEE, coupled with hands-on projects during my internship at BSNL, has given me a good understanding on IoT and edge computing. I've worked on innovative projects like a CNN-based face recognition system and a density-based traffic control system, showcasing my ability to bridge the gap between hardware and software in data-driven solutions.

I'm proficient in a wide range of technologies, including Python, SQL, Azure cloud services, and IoT platforms. My experience spans from developing ETL pipelines and crafting data visualizations to implementing machine learning models for real-world applications.
As a Microsoft Certified Azure Data Engineer Associate, I'm passionate about leveraging cloud technologies to create scalable, efficient data solutions. I'm always eager to take on new challenges that allow me to apply my diverse skill set in data engineering, analytics, and IoT integration.

I'm looking for opportunities to contribute to innovative projects that push the boundaries of data engineering, particularly those that intersect with IoT and smart systems. Let's connect if you're working on exciting data challenges that could benefit from my unique blend of skills!

Languages: Python, SQL, TSQL, Scala, Java, R, PHP, Jenkins, C++
Tools: Databricks, Hive, Hadoop, Stream Analytics, Drupal, Talend, ADF, Alteryx, Tableau, Power BI, ERStudio, Apache Nifi, Spark, Kafka , Amazon Redshift, RDS, Athena
Databases: DynamoDB , CosmosDB, ArrangoDB, Cassandra, AzureSQL, ADLS Gen2, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Synapse, DBeaver

projects.description:
- Spearheaded data preprocessing by handling null values, standardizing formats, and engineering new features like "Dose_mg" from product titles using Python regex, enabling dosage-specific insights for downstream analysis.  
- Performed comprehensive exploratory data analysis (EDA) using univariate, bivariate, and multivariate approaches. Univariate analysis identified 5 mg as the most consumed dosage and highlighted brand-wise product distribution. Bivariate analysis revealed that "Nature's Perfect Night" had the most consistent high review scores, while multivariate analysis correlated review sentiment with flavor, dosage, and form, uncovering that tablets of strawberry flavor had the highest satisfaction scores.  
- Built a robust NLP pipeline for sentiment analysis, extracting polarity, subjectivity, and consumer sentiment trends. Leveraged N-grams (bigrams and trigrams) to identify key consumer behavior phrases like "fall asleep fast" and "help sleep better," while word cloud analysis revealed dominant positive terms like "good," "great," and "help," underscoring strong customer approval.  
- Delivered actionable business insights by identifying 5 mg as the preferred dosage, tracking a 60x surge in consumer reviews from 2010 to 2024, and highlighting that 80% of users recommended melatonin products.  
- Analysis of user behavior indicated that most users consume melatonin 20 minutes before bed, shaping product usage recommendations and strategic messaging for stakeholders.

projects.description:
a comprehensive analysis and visualization endeavor that leverages an extensive dataset of 311 service requests from Kansas City, spanning from 2007 to March 2021. This project exemplifies the power of data to uncover insights and inform decision-making processes within municipal services.
Key Achievements:
Data Profiling & Integrity Analysis: Utilized Alteryx,ydataprofilling and Talend Prep Builder to profile the dataset, identifying,understanding the data behaviour for transformations  and documenting key data quality issues such as missing values, duplicates, and inconsistencies, setting a strong foundation for accurate analysis.
Database Integration: Using Talend Data Studio, successfully staged,denormalized for analytics and integrated cleaned data into Dimensional Model, creating 6 tables out of this dataset, including Azure SQL and SSMS, ensuring seamless data accessibility,readability and management .
Dynamic Visualizations: Developed insightful dashboards in Power BI and Tableau, revealing trends and patterns in service requests over time, source, departmental workloads, and response times, among others.
Geospatial Analysis: Highlighted geographical distribution of service requests, pinpointing areas with the highest demand, aiding in resource allocation and planning.
Efficiency & Performance Metrics: Evaluated departmental workloads and response efficiency, offering valuable metrics for improving city services and response strategies.
Tools & Technologies Used:
Alteryx,ydataprofilling and Tablue Prep Builder for data preparation and profiling
SSMS and Azure Data Studio for database management
Power BI and Tableau for advanced data visualization and dashboard creation
projects.title: End-to-End Data Analysis and Visualization Project: Insights from Kansas City's 311 Service Requests (2007-2021)
